quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  61,10,O you who have faith! Shall I show you a deal that will deliver you from a painful punishment
  61,11,"Have faith in Allah and His Apostle, and wage jihad in the way of Allah with your persons and possessions. That is better for you, should you know"
  61,12,"He will forgive your sins and admit you into gardens with streams running in them, and into good dwellings in the Gardens of Eden; that is the great success"
  61,13,"And other [blessings] you cherish: help from Allah and a victory near at hand, and give good news to the faithful"
  61,14,"O you who have faith! Be Allah’s helpers, just as Jesus son of Mary said to his disciples, ‘Who will be my helpers for Allah’s sake?’ The Disciples said, ‘We will be Allah’s helpers!’ So a group of the Children of Israel believed, and a group disbelieved. Then We strengthened the faithful against their enemies, and they came to prevail [over them]"